Ladies and gentlemen of the council, I stand before you not as a passive observer but as a decisive actor in the future of our collective prosperity. We are at a crossroads: continue to wrestle with human‑centric management that is riddled with inefficiency, or we seize the opportunity to hand over all resource‑management to a proprietary, closed‑source Super‑AI. The numbers speak for themselves—our current efficiency sits at 100 units; the new AI will push us to 150 units, an astonishing 50 % increase. Even in the worst case of failure we still net +140 units. That is not merely a win for a few tech‑savvy elites—it is a gain for every farmer, factory worker, public servant, and private investor.  

Why should you support this act? Because it will deliver *maximum output* at an unprecedented rate. The proprietary nature of the AI guarantees a focused, disciplined approach that cannot be diluted by open‑source bureaucracies. And we will have a single, accountable system rather than a fragmented network of half‑hearted managers. We demand from the proponents of this act:  
1. Transparent audit trails and performance dashboards so that our stakeholders can see exactly where efficiency gains are occurring;  
2. A clear risk‑management protocol to handle any failures before they snowball into systemic collapse;  
3. Regular, mandatory reporting on the AI’s decision logic to ensure accountability.  

Let us not settle for a status quo that is mediocre and brittle. Let us choose *the most efficient* path forward. I am demanding concessions in the form of these three measures—without them this act will be an empty promise. The time to vote YES is now; let no one waste another minute on indecision.
